<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<%- include('../partials/head') %>
<body class="page page--<%= pageClass %>">
<%- include('../partials/header') %>
<main id="main" class="main main--product">

  <section class="scene scene--hero scene--eden">
    <div class="scene__glow scene__glow--eden" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="container scene__inner">
      <p class="eyebrow reveal" data-reveal>Eden</p>
      <h1 class="scene__title reveal" data-reveal><%= PRODUCTS.eden.headline %></h1>
      <p class="scene__lead reveal" data-reveal><%= PRODUCTS.eden.subhead %></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scene scene--split">
    <div class="container scene__split">
      <div class="scene__visual reveal" data-reveal>
        <div class="scene__panel scene__panel--eden" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="scene__rings"></span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="scene__copy reveal" data-reveal>
        <h2 class="scene__h">Research software—not a feature inside finance</h2>
        <p>Eden is its own product: a local-first system for aggregating, analyzing, prioritizing, and evaluating sources. It does not “belong to” CFO or Ledger; it addresses a different class of work entirely.</p>
        <p>Content is broken into claims, facts, and context. Summaries stay tied to sources. Outputs are structured so you can see where each piece came from.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scene scene--feature">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h2 class="scene__h scene__h--center reveal" data-reveal>What Eden ingests</h2>
      <ul class="scene__list reveal" data-reveal style="max-width: 46ch; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
        <li>Screen recordings</li>
        <li>Videos—local files or from platforms such as YouTube, Rumble, Vimeo, Instagram (public/free content)</li>
        <li>Articles and written material</li>
        <li>Images and screenshots</li>
        <li>Your own files alongside material you point it at</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="scene__center reveal" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">Eden transcribes audio, extracts text with OCR, and compiles structured research outputs with citations.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scene scene--split scene--reverse">
    <div class="container scene__split">
      <div class="scene__copy reveal" data-reveal>
        <h2 class="scene__h"><%= SITE.steward.name %> prioritizes what matters to you</h2>
        <p>Steward is logic-driven, not open-ended generation. In Eden it helps prioritize facts using <em>your</em> context—so the same corpus can be ordered differently for different questions.</p>
        <p>Sources are evaluated for consistency, evidence support, cross-source agreement, and relevance to your situation. Eden does not replace your judgment; it makes the landscape legible.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="scene__visual reveal" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
        <div class="scene__panel scene__panel--layers" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scene scene--split">
    <div class="container scene__split">
      <div class="scene__visual reveal" data-reveal>
        <div class="scene__panel scene__panel--stripes" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="scene__copy reveal" data-reveal>
        <h2 class="scene__h">What Eden is not</h2>
        <ul class="scene__list">
          <li>It does not write papers or replace authorship.</li>
          <li>It does not make subjective judgments about people.</li>
          <li>It does not bypass paywalls or access restricted content.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scene scene--ecosystem">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="scene__h reveal" data-reveal>Related products, separate missions</h2>
      <p class="scene__lead reveal" data-reveal><strong>CFO</strong> is the financial operating system. <strong>Ledger</strong> is the identity vault and deterministic document layer. Eden shares Steward with them but answers a different question: how to turn diverse sources into prioritized, citable research—on your machine, under your control.</p>
      <div class="ecosystem-links reveal" data-reveal>
        <a href="product-cfo.html" class="ecosystem-links__a">CFO</a>
        <a href="product-ledger.html" class="ecosystem-links__a">Ledger</a>
        <a href="compare.html" class="ecosystem-links__a">Compare all</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%- include('../partials/availability-status') %>

</main>
<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
<%- include('../partials/mobile-nav') %>
<script type="module" src="/src/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
